body:
by **pauli.rikula**:

<pre>Is there any way to have an array which size exceeds int's maximum value?

The maximum size of arrays should be mentioned in
<a href="http://golang.org/doc/go_spec.html#Array_types">http://golang.org/doc/go_spec.html#Array_types</a> 

in my computer:

var d [2147483648]*uint8;
--&gt; 
testlimits.go:11: array bound must be non-negative

and
var e [4294967296]*uint8;
fmt.Printf(&quot;len of e:%v\n&quot;,len(e));
--&gt;
len of e:0</pre>
